280            /**
281            * This value tracks the depth of a switch expression. Along with the
282            * IDENT to id rule at the end of the parser, this value helps us
283            * to know if the "yield" we are parsing is an IDENT, method call, class,
284            * field, etc. or if it is a java 13+ yield statement. Positive values
285            * indicate that we are within a (possibly nested) switch expression.
286            */
287            private int switchBlockDepth = 0;
288
289            /**
290             * Checks if next statement is a yield statement.
291             *
292             * @return true if next statement is a yield statement.
293             */
294            private boolean isYieldStatement() {
295                return _input.LT(1).getType() == JavaLanguageLexer.LITERAL_YIELD && switchBlockDepth > 0;
296            }
